f the same year Lucas records \"Bonvin delivered the 12th flower for W's - paid him the remaining 100 fs making 300 fs for the 12\" (Randall, Diary of George A. Lucas, vol. 2, p. 163).[2] In a diary entry for 10 February 1863 Lucas records \"Bonvin to see me took fruit for Graham\" \"Bonvin 2 drawings apples oranges 30 fs.\" This is one of four watercolors of apples by Bonvin dating from or before this date, it is therefore possible that William T. Walters later acquired this watercolor from his Baltimore neighbor.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.1651","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS4_37.1651_Fnt_DD_AT21_23636-tms.jpg"},{"ObjectID":34203,"Title":"Portrait of Mrs. Decatur Howard Miller (Eliza Credilla Hare)","Artist":"Alfred Jacob Miller (American, 1810-1874)","Date":"ca. 1850","Medium":"oil on canvas","CreditLine":"given to Walters Art Museum, 1978.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/37.2557","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PL1_37.2557_Fnt_TR_C81III.jpg"},{"ObjectID":83647,"Title":"Nushabah Entertained by Alexander the Great","Artist":"Nizami Ganjavi (Azerbaijani, died 605 AH/AD 1209)","Date":"11th century AH/AD 17th century (Safavid)","Medium":"ink and pigments on paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1931, by bequest.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/W.612.288B","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/CPS_W.612.288b_Fp_DD.jpg"},{"ObjectID":25743,"Title":"Nogaku zue","Artist":"Sakamaki Kogyo (Japanese, 1869-1927); Matsuke Heikichi (Japanese)","Date":"1899 (Meiji)","Medium":"pigments on mulberry paper","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1989, by gift.","URL":"https://purl.thewalters.org/art/95.260","ImageURL":"https://art.thewalters.org/images/raw/PS3_95.260_Fnt_DD_JP09-2.jpg"},{"ObjectID":28939,"Title":"Cylinder Seal with a Contest Scene","Artist":"Neo-Assyrian","Date":"ca. 911-612 BCE (Neo-Assyrian)","Medium":"chalcedony","CreditLine":"Walters Art Museum, 1941, by purchase.","URL":"https://p